Inter-Service Communication


Synchronous Communication
HTTP/REST for real-time requests

// Service-to-service HTTP call
const response = await fetch(`${AI_SERVICE_URL}/api/analyze-content`, {
  method: 'POST',
  headers: {
    'Content-Type': 'application/json',
    'Authorization': `Bearer ${serviceToken}`
  },
  body: JSON.stringify({ content, type: 'travel-post' })
});



Asynchronous Communication
Message queues for background processing

// Redis pub/sub for async communication
import Redis from 'ioredis';

const redis = new Redis(process.env.REDIS_URL);

// Publisher (Travel Content Service)
await redis.publish('content.created', JSON.stringify({
  postId: newPost.id,
  content: newPost.content,
  timestamp: new Date().toISOString()
}));

// Subscriber (AI Curation Service)
redis.subscribe('content.created');
redis.on('message', async (channel, message) => {
  const data = JSON.parse(message);
  await processContentForAI(data);
});





Database per Service Pattern


Travel Content Service
PostgreSQL - Relational data for posts, users, locations


AI Curation Service
MongoDB - Document storage for AI analysis results


Media Processing Service
S3 + Redis - Object storage + metadata caching


Web Scraping Service
MongoDB - Flexible schema for scraped content

